==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Horsefly
<hw>Horse"fly`</hw> <pr>(h⟦ocir⟧rs"fl⟦imac⟧`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Horseflies</plw>
<pr>(h⟦ocir⟧rs"fl⟦imac⟧z`)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any dipterous fly of the family <fam>Tabanidae</fam>, that stings
horses, and sucks their blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Of these flies there are numerous species, both in
Europe and America. They have a large proboscis with four sharp lancets
for piercing the skin. Called also <altname>breeze fly</altname>. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Diptera</er>, and <er>Breeze
fly</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The horse tick or forest fly
(<gen>Hippobosca</gen>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Horsefoot</ent>⟦br⟧
